"{\"uid\": \"si.com-high-school-michigan-michigan-high-school-athletes-competing-in-the-2024-paris-olympics-01j3qm465t77\", \"text\": \"The 2024 Paris Olympic games are officially underway as athletes from around the world compete in France.  Thirteen athletes who attendedMichigan high schoolswill compete for Olympic glory in the 2024 Paris summer games. For many of these athletes, competing in Michiganhigh school sportswas a part of their journey to the 2024 Paris Olympics.  Here are the athletes fromMichigancompeting in the 2024 Paris Olympics.  Abby Tamer \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Whitmore Lake \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Field Hockey  Tamer is a graduate fromDexter High School, and he was a four-time Michigan All-State first team selection (2017, '18, '19, '20). Tamer is a senior at the University of Michigan, and she's been on the NFHCA Collegiate National Academic Team.\\u00c2  Team USA women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s field hockey begins on July 27 against Argentina at 1:45 p.m. ET.  Devin Booker \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Grand Rapids \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Basketball  Booker was born in Grand Rapids, and he attendedGrandville High Schooluntil he moved to Mississippi before his sophomore season. Booker played on freshman, junior varsity and varsity for Grandville during his freshman year.  Heath Baldwin \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Kalamazoo \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Track and Field  Baldwin is a Kalamazoo native who went toHackett Catholic Central. Baldwin won the decathlon at the 2024 U.S. Olympic Trials in Eugene, Oregon. He started his career at the University of Michigan before he transferred to Michigan State.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m pretty young. And if I can get a medal and gain some experience, too, I think that'll be a win. But I have gone into every meet this year hoping to win. So I mean, obviously, the main goal is to take my best shot at winning,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Baldwin told theLansing State Journal.\\u00c2  The decathlon begins on August 2 at 4:05 a.m.  Adam Coon \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Fowlerville \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Wrestling  Coon will compete in the 130kg weight class in the Paris Olympics. He attendedFowlerville High School, where he was a four-time state champion, winning at 215 pounds (2010, '11) and 285 pounds (2012, '13).  Greco-Roman 130kg wrestling begins on August 5 at 9 a.m.  Aaron Cummings \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Muskegon \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Rugby  Cummings started his rugby career atGrand Haven High School. He excelled at Davenport University, and he plays professionally for the Chicago Lions.\\u00c2  Rugby 7s began on July 24.  Andrew Evans \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Portage \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Track and Field  Evans is aPortage Northern High Schoolgraduate competing in the discus throw. He was first at the U.S. Olympic Trials with a throw of 218 feet and six inches. It will be his second Olympics. He qualified in 2016 for the Rio Olympics.\\u00c2  Men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s discus throw begins on August 5 at 4:10 p.m.  Grant Fisher \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Grand Blanc \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Track and Field  TheGrand Blancnative ran a sub-4 mile while in high school, and he was a two-time Foot Locker national cross country champion. Fisher competed in the 2020 Tokyo Olympics, and he finished fifth in the 10000m and ninth in the 5000m. He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll be running the same events in 2024.  The men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 10000m will be on August 2 at 3:20 p.m. The men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 5000m begins on August 7 at 5:10 a.m.  Zach Hammer \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Ann Arbor \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Sport Climbing  Hammer graduated fromSkyline High Schoolthis summer. He will compete in speed climbing at the Paris Olympics. It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the second time speed climbing will be an Olympic sport having debuted at the Tokyo Olympics.  Speed climbing begins on August 6 at 7 a.m.  Hobbs Kessler \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Ann Arbor \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Track and Field  Kessler is the second Skyline High School graduate in the 2024 Paris Olympics. He broke the U.S. high school indoor mile record while he was an Eagle. Kessler trains in Ann Arbor for the Very Nice Track Club.\\u00c2  Kessler will compete in the 1500m. The first round is on August 2 at 5:05 a.m.  Sorin Koszyk \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Grosse Pointe Park \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Rowing  Koszyk started his rowing career as a freshman while atGrosse Pointe South High School. He rowed for four years at the Detroit Boat Club before rowing for Cornell, where he was First Team All Ivy League.\\u00c2  Koszyk will compete in the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s double sculls which begins on July 27 at 5:30 a.m.  Alena Olsen \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Caledonia \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Rugby  Olsen didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t begin playing rugby until she attended the University of Michigan. She became an All-American during her time as a Wolverine.\\u00c2  Women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s rugby begins on July 28.  Hannah Robersts \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Buchanan \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Cycling  Roberts attendedBuchanan High School, and she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll represent Team USA in women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s park BMX freestyle. Roberts won a silver medal in the event in the 2020 Tokyo Olympics.  Women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s park BMX freestyle begins on July 20 at 7:25 a.m.  Grace Stark \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 White Bear \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 Track and Field  Stark attendedLakeland High Schooland won three individual state championships. She attended the University of Florida, and she finished her career as a 2024 NCAA outdoor champion in the 100m hurdles.  The women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100m hurdles begins on August 2 at 4:35 a.m.  To get live updates on your phone - as well as follow your favorite teams and top games - you can download the SBLive Sports app:\\u00c2Download iPhone App|\\u00c2\\u00a0Download Android App  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 Jack Butler | butler@scorebooklive.com |\\u00c2@Butler917\\u00c2\\u00a0on X  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Jack Butler is the Regional Editor of the Midwest for SBLive/High School on SI. Jack has covered high school sports in Oregon, Arizona and Minnesota.  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC. - All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands. All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\"}"